new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..fd2d4a7133
--- /dev/null
+++ b/.changeset/anonymous-terms-acceptance.md
@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@
+---
+"wrangler": patch
+---
+
+Require explicit Terms of Service acceptance for `--temporary`
+
+Wrangler now prompts users to type `yes` before continuing with `--temporary`, including in non-interactive environments. The prompt links to Cloudflare's Terms of Service and Privacy Policy, explains that anything deployed with `--temporary` may expire unless it is claimed before expiry, and the flag uses a temporary preview account in interactive terminals instead of starting OAuth.
